challengeName: Release Assembly - MTurk Admin Web Dashboard
detailedRequirements:
Project Overview

Our client want to use Amazon mturk to invite game players to play set of games. Each Human Intelligence Task (HIT) will be for completing a "task" (analogous to a subset of levels in the game versions) in exchange for payment. Ideally, we would keep this as short and simple as possible - i.e. one "task" gets the payment (instead of multiple progressive levels).

Game players will need to navigate to client website in order to play the games, client will use mturk API to login players, and to perform some other mturk operations. Also client wants to allow multiple teams to use same mturk account but with limited access. We are launching multiple challenges to build the infrastructure to automate and simplify this process.

Challenge Task Overview

We are building the admin web dashboard in this challenge. We have completed the first change of mturk API, the admin web dashboard will be using that API.

You will address the following in this challenge :

  • Use Express.js web framework with simple responsive UI using bootstrap framework. Boostrap allows you to build simple responsive UI without much efforts, we are targeting both mobile and desktop versions for the web app.
    • The application will be separated from mTurk API code base and will be deployed independently.
    • The UI should be simple and contains the following :
      • Landing page :
        • Contains a Logo, and welcome banner .
        • Button to login.
      • Dashboard page :
        • A Hits listing table :
          • It includes 'Hit Id', 'Hit Title', 'Domain Id', 'Task Id', 'Last Updateder' and 'Action columns.
          • Hit Id and Title columns linked to Details page.
        • Button to create new hit
      • Details page :
        • Buttons to extend, disable or create new hit.
        • Form include all information returned by the mturk API, should be well displayed, you should use proper UI component.
      • Create Hit Page :
        • Allows to create new hit
        • It accepts all fields from http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSMechTurk/latest/AWSMturkAPI/ApiReference_CreateHITOperation.html in addition to taskId used by mturk API to associate the created hit with the game task.
        • Use proper UI components to allow user create the hit easily, use 'add more', tables, panels, drop down lists ..etc. To simplify the creation process.
      • Extend Hit :
        • Allow extending the hit
        • It accepts fields from http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSMechTurk/latest/AWSMturkAPI/ApiReference_ExtendHITOperation.html
        • Use proper UI components for each field needed to extend a hit.
      • Disable Hit :
        • This one will show a popup modal to use to confirm if they want to disable hit or not.
        • It should have two buttons : confirm and cancel.
      • Common Sections :
        • Header - contains logo placeholder and logout button
        • Welcome message with basic instructions (make these placholders for now), each page will have it's own welcome message instructions.
        • Footer - Simple copyright statement
  • The web application will provide the following functionality :
    • Login : The web app will allow users to login to mTurk API OAuth server to login.
      • The app will display a login button, it will take user through the OAuth 2.0 Authorization Code Grant flow provided by mTurk API.
      • The exchange of access token should be done via backend. Secret key should not be stored or exposed in the client side of the web application.
    • Hits Listing : The user will be able to see all the Hits to which they belong (for which their account has an associated domain) to.
      • Use "GET /domain/:id/hits" endpoint by mturk API to get the Hits list
      • You can find the API call and how to test this endpoint by importing the postman.json provided in the mTurk API application code base to Postman - Rest client application.
    • Creating Hit : The user can also create new hit.
      • Use "POST  /domain/:id/hits" endpoint by mturk API to create new hit under the passed domain.
      • You can find the API call and how to test this endpoint by importing the postman.json provided in the mturk API application code base to Postman - Rest client application.
      • The input to this method is taskId in addition to fields from http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSMechTurk/latest/AWSMturkAPI/ApiReference_CreateHITOperation.html 
    • Extend Hit : the user can extend the hit
      • Use "POST /hit/:id" to extend the hit.
      • It expects the fields http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSMechTurk/latest/AWSMturkAPI/ApiReference_ExtendHITOperation.html
    • Disabling Hit : the user can disable a hit so it is no more active in mturk.com
      • Use "DELETE /hit/:id" to disable a hit.
  • Provide a readme file for details about deploying the application, configuring it, and testing locally.

Folder Structure

  • Root directory
    • env-sample (this will be a sample of .env file)
    • app.js
    • models
    • views
    • controllers
    • public
      • css
      • js
      • i
    • .gitignore
    • config/ folder
    • READ.md
    • anything else needed.

Technology Overview

  • NodeJS
  • Express.JS
  • PostgreSQL
  • AJAX
  • HTML
  • CSS
  • Bootstrap

Source Code

Code exists in private github repository, request access in challenge forums if you don't see it or if you get 404 not found error.

Private github repo https://github.com/topcoderinc/csfv_mturk_api
finalSubmissionGuidelines:
Submission Deliverables

Below is an overview of the deliverables:

  • a git folder with same structure as outlined above.
  • A readme.md file detailing all information needed to setup and run the admin web dashboard. Use github flavored markup text. It should be part of the git folder submitted
  • text file with any notes to reviewer.
  • You don't need to submit a word document for deployment guide.
  • Submitting a video for how to setup and test api is a plus.

Final Submission

For each member, the final submission should be uploaded via the challenge detail page on topcoder.com.
